description.narrative: (Rwanda): Rwanda Health Family Project (RFHP) will support interventions to improve access to clinical and community child and maternal health services. Areas of support include: emergency neonatal and obstetric care, focused antenatal care, and verbal autopsy. RFHP will support access to neonatal services such as: essential newborn care, emergency triage assessment and treatment, and newborn death audit, including stillbirth audit. Support will improve access to child care services at the facility and community through training, equipment, coaching and supervision of community health workers (CHW) and facility providers. The project will continue to roll out community-based provision of family planning products. In addition to the community package, the activity will support cooperatives for CHWs to explore options for improving their income-generating abilities and opportunities. In 19 districts, capacity building of facility quality committees and district management teams will be strengthened to implement policies and manage services.
